<paragraph id="8BE95B6C554AB030078757B5FB47F7C3" blockId="6.[166,1225,909,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
<keyLead id="30A7F859554AB030078757B5FB47F7C3" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
1. External lateral carina of pronotum above the tegmen strongly curved upward, arch-like (
<figureCitation id="136D47E9554AB030031E57B5FB08F7A0" box="[1087,1158,909,931]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[204,1196,178,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[196,1210,174,1458]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1–13. Yunnantettix thaicus sp. n.: 1 — male head and pronotum, lateral view; 2 — female anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; 3 — male head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; 4 — male head, frontal view; 5 — female antenna, dorsal view; 6 — male hind femur, lateral view; 7 — male fore femur, lateral view; 8 — male hind tarsus, lateral view; 9 — male apex of abdomen, lateral view; 10 — the same, dorsal view; 11 — the same, ventral view; 12 — female apex of abdomen, lateral view; 13 — female 7th sternite and subgenital plate, ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452361/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">fig. 1, 2</figureCitation>
). Apex of posterior pronotal process with shallow excision. ........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5620EF554AB03004E95792FB1EF7C3" authority="Storozhenko &amp; Pushkar, 2015" authorityName="Storozhenko &amp; Pushkar" authorityYear="2015" box="[968,1168,938,960]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Yunnantettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thaicus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B922877E554AB03004E95792FB1EF7C3" box="[968,1168,938,960]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Yunnantettix thaicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2113A05554AB03003B75792FB47F7C3" box="[1174,1225,938,960]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE95B6C554AB030078757FFFB47F7F9" blockId="6.[166,1225,909,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
<keyLead id="30A7F859554AB030078757FFFB47F7F9" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
— External carina of pronotum above the tegmen only slightly curved upward or almost straight (
<figureCitation id="136D47E9554AB03003A657FFFE82F7F9" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,817,839]" captionTargetBox="[206,1186,187,753]" captionTargetId="figure-339@5.[204,1201,174,762]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 16–20. Yunnantettix bannanensis, male (16–17) and Y. elytratus, female (18–20): 16, 18 — head and pronotum, lateral view; 17 — body, dorsal view; 19 — head and pronotum, dorsal view; 20 — head, frontal view (16–17 after Zheng, 1995; 18–19 after Günther, 1939, with modification; 20 after Shishodia, 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452365/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">fig. 16, 18</figureCitation>
). Apex of posterior pronotal process with deep excision or rounded (
<figureCitation id="136D47E9554AB030048057DCFB8FF7F9" box="[929,1025,996,1018]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,817,839]" captionTargetBox="[206,1186,187,753]" captionTargetId="figure-339@5.[204,1201,174,762]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 16–20. Yunnantettix bannanensis, male (16–17) and Y. elytratus, female (18–20): 16, 18 — head and pronotum, lateral view; 17 — body, dorsal view; 19 — head and pronotum, dorsal view; 20 — head, frontal view (16–17 after Zheng, 1995; 18–19 after Günther, 1939, with modification; 20 after Shishodia, 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452365/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">fig. 17, 19</figureCitation>
). .............................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
